rComments: At first I didnt know anything about this class and only took it because it fit my schedule. I am glad I did because I now am thinking about going into urban planning. Dr Spinks is a very inspirational professor. She took material that could have easily been boring and made me want to learn it. Tip: go to class. The exam is all from lectures.
Lots to read but it is doable. Marks are fair and she is an amazing lecturer. Seems very passionate about the subject and is quite a wealth of knowledge on contemporary urban issues.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: My initial impression of Dr. Spinks and this course was not very good - I only took the class because it fit with my schedule. But, she is very approachable and accessible outside of class. She wants you to succeed and is very interested in the subject matter. I would recommend her to anyone interested in urban planning in particular
